description:
Hey friends! Welcome back to another episode of holy girl diaries where I will show you high protein, healthy and easy recipes you can make! I am really focusing on healthy, high-protein recipes that are still yummy. I want to share recipes for you that are simple, healthy and tasty. We are all going to enter our cooking era, together ü§ç I hope you guys enjoy these recipes and let me know if you try them!

RECIPES:

Protein Pudding 
- 1 scoop chocolate pb protein powder https://amzn.to/3S0UfTF
- 1 scoop chocolate coconut greens https://go.shopmy.us/p-6208309
- 1 scoop collagen https://go.shopmy.us/p-4374177
- 1/4 cup mixed frozen berries 
- 1/3 cup purely elizabeth granola 
- 1 tbsp pb 

protein: 30 g

Pancake Bowl
- 1/4 cup low carb pancake mix  https://amzn.to/4613yZs
- 1/2 cup egg whites 
- 1 scoop pb protein powder https://go.shopmy.us/p-4194425
- 1 scoop chocolate greens https://go.shopmy.us/p-4194346 
- 1/3 ripe banana 
- top with 1/4 cup fresh fruit, 1/2 1/3 cup granola, 1/2 tbsp maple syrup  


protein: 35g protein

Sweet Potato Burger Sliders 
- 1 sweet potato 
- 4 oz ground beef 
- burger seasoning 
- lettuce 
- red onion 
- pickles 
- side dish chipotle mayo 

Kelp Noodle Bowl 
- kelp noodles https://amzn.to/4bFuuiH 
- mushrooms 
- broccoli 
- carrots
- olive oil
- chicken 
sauce: 
- coconut aminos (1/3 cup) 
- sesame oil (1 tbsp) 
- garlic (1 clove)
- sesame seeds 

Cottage Cheese Cookie Dough 
- 1/2 cup low fat cottage cheese
- 1 scoop chocolate greens https://go.shopmy.us/p-4194346 
- 1 tbsp maple syrup
- 1 tsp vanilla extract 
- 2 tbsp almond flour 
- 1 scoop peanut butter protein powder https://go.shopmy.us/p-4194425
- Top with 1 tbsp chocolate chips 

protein: 30 g

description:
1. Be honest with God about where you are at in your waiting season.¬†
2. Thanking God and showing gratitude each day.¬†
3. Taking all of your worries to prayer.¬†
4. Surround yourself with Christian community.¬†

8. Journal through your thoughts and feelings about this season and what you're looking forward to.¬†
9. Create a monthly prayer board that will encourage and uplift you.¬†
10. Look for opportunities to serve / volunteer in your community or in your local church.

title: Christian books you need ‚ô°  #girls #shorts #relatable #christian
description:
I have always loved reading - but just in the last few years have I truly fallen in love with good Christian books.¬†

There are so many incredible books with wisdom on how to grow closer to God and truly reach your full potential in Him. There are so many incredible mentors we can learn from through reading a book. We must commit to going to God‚Äôs word over any author, but let‚Äôs not neglect the way God is moving through people to reach us and share truth with us.¬†
Here are some of my go-tos:¬†

1. This Present Darkness (Frank E. Peretti) - This book completely changed the way I look at spiritual warfare. It was through this book (even though it‚Äôs completely fictional) that my eyes were opened to the spiritual battle we face on a daily basis, that we can‚Äôt even see. This book showed me the power of prayer and how I must go to the Word and prayer as my first line of defense when it comes to spiritual attacks. Also - be ready to stay up late reading this one. I couldn‚Äôt put it down!¬†

2. The Purpose Driven Life (Rick Warren) - This book was the very first book I read about God. It was a 40 day devotional that helped me get to know God from ground zero. I kid you not - I had no knowledge of who God was or how to truly center my life around my faith. This book broke it down so practically that it actually helped change my life completely, and start a whole new chapter with God.¬†

3. Ruthless Elimination of Hurry (John Mark Comer) - I love how practical this book is, when it comes to bringing us back to rest and Sabbath. This book showed me that I am so much more than what I do. And that I don‚Äôt need to allow what I do or the successes and failures of my life to define me. I love how funny and practical this book is. I‚Äôm not kidding - I think I read this in a week! It will help you prioritize rest in your life and help you feel refreshed in Christ.¬†

¬†I just wrote my very first book, the Joy Of The In-Between, and I‚Äôm giving away some free bonuses if you pre-order!¬†

¬†I‚Äôm giving away a 10-part bonus bible study series on being in a waiting season, plus the first 30 devos of this book, when you pre-order my new book.

Head to the link in my bio and I‚Äôll send you the link to pre-order and fill out the form, and you‚Äôll get all your goodies today! ‚ú®¬†
